00:10:35.170 --> 00:10:43.360
Looking at the history, it
seems that the recent shift

00:10:43.360 --> 00:10:49.370
in the correctional population
under incarceration started

00:10:49.370 --> 00:10:53.440
with the reduction in the
number of beds available

00:10:53.440 --> 00:10:57.870
in the states' [inaudible] network.

00:10:57.870 --> 00:11:04.490
The de-institutionalization
of people

00:11:04.490 --> 00:11:11.950
with severe mental illness began
in the mid 1950s around the time

00:11:11.950 --> 00:11:15.660
when the first important
anti-psychotic medication,

00:11:15.660 --> 00:11:20.790
named Thorazine, became
available in the United States.

00:11:20.790 --> 00:11:29.080
The de-institutionalization was
accelerated in the mid 1960s

00:11:29.080 --> 00:11:35.330
in connection with federal
incentives and court decisions.

00:11:35.330 --> 00:11:42.940
This process led to the
disappearance of more than 90%

00:11:42.940 --> 00:11:47.510
of the state psychiatric beds
for long term care in the US.

00:11:47.510 --> 00:11:55.970
The advocate of the
de-institutionalization believed

00:11:55.970 --> 00:12:00.360
that the closing of said hospitals
would encourage the mentally ill

00:12:00.360 --> 00:12:03.990
population to live
more independently

00:12:03.990 --> 00:12:08.900
in the community while
treatment will be provided

00:12:08.900 --> 00:12:12.580
by community health programs.

00:12:12.580 --> 00:12:17.160
Unfortunately, the federal
government did not provide

00:12:17.160 --> 00:12:21.380
sufficient funds for
community programs

00:12:21.380 --> 00:12:26.020
to meet the increased
demand for services,

00:12:26.020 --> 00:12:32.120
and the states were not able
to fill the financial gap.

00:12:32.120 --> 00:12:37.580
As a result of this lack of service
availability, hundreds of thousands

00:12:37.580 --> 00:12:39.860
of mentally released

00:12:39.860 --> 00:12:44.510
in the community did not
have access to treatment.

00:12:44.510 --> 00:12:50.340
These individuals were involved in
substance abuse and misdemeanors,

00:12:50.340 --> 00:12:54.800
and they ended up serving
time in our jails and prison,

00:12:54.800 --> 00:13:01.570 position:56%
